OL,3,C'Don't turn your back on us': Farmers
OL,4,CUnion message to government
OL,6,FSpeaking at the Labour Party
OL,7,FConference, Environment Secretary
OL,8,FSteve Reed said: "We will back farmers
OL,9,Fin the fantastic work they do to feed
OL,10,Four nation and we'll work with them to
OL,11,Frestore nature and stop animal waste
OL,12,Ffertiliser and pesticide pollution
OL,13,Frunning into our waterways."
OL,15,FTom Bradshaw, President of the
OL,16,FNational Farmers Union said: "What I
OL,17,Fwould say to the government is we see
OL,18,Fthe challenges around the world `
OL,19,Fwhether that be war in Eastern Europe,
OL,20,Fthe Middle East as it is today or
OL,21,Fclimate change taking hold.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
